    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-16T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-16T11:00:00-05:00" n="263"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d263">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.01/57: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-16T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 16, 1937—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>101. From Braden. It would be appreciated if the Department could give me some
                    indication as to whether it considers formal recognition of the Busch régime in
                    Bolivia to be necessary. [Braden.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
